=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Convert 3-(trifluoromethyl)aniline (Nc1cccc(C(F)(F)F)c1) to the N-aryl urea fragment N-(3-trifluoromethylphenyl)urea, Nc1cccc(C(F)(F)F)c1NC(N)=O, e.g. with NaOCN/HCl (or equivalent urea-forming conditions). | Step 2: Subject N-(3-trifluoromethylphenyl)urea, 4-formylbenzonitrile (N#Cc1ccc(C=O)cc1), and ethyl acetoacetate to a Biginelli-type cyclocondensation (acid, heat) to give the ethyl ester intermediate CCOC(=O)C1=C(C)NC(c2ccc(C#N)cc2)NC(=O)N1c1cccc(C(F)(F)F)c1. | Step 3: Hydrolyze the C5 ethyl ester (NaOH or LiOH, aq. alcohol/THF, then acidify) to furnish the target acid CC1=C(C(=O)O)C(c2ccc(C#N)cc2)NC(=O)N1c1cccc(C(F)(F)F)c1.

